<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-419-684  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 419 684.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  May 7 1990 v7 n18 p12(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>How to install EE 1.2 printer drivers. (Extended Edition)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Holmes, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (products).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Product:   OS/2 Extended Edition 1.2 (Operating system) (usage).andO;Topic:     TutorialPrintersDrives.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>The following procedure sets up a new printer driver, such as the HPPCL5.DRVdriver, in OS/2 Extended Edition 1.2.andP;  This supersedes the procedure outlinedin IBM's documentation, which does not work reliably.andM;Copy any necessary dynamic link library (DLL) files to the C:OS2DLLsubdirectory.andP;  For a new Hewlett-Packard Co.andP;  LaserJet III driver, thesefiles are called HPPCL5FL.DLL and HPPCL5PL.DLL.andP;  For the other driver that isshipped with IBM's OS/2, these files are called GENERIC.DLL and HPADDF.DLL.andM;Next, in IBM's DeskTop Manager utility program, choose the Utilities group,Control Panel, Installation and Add Printer Driver menu selections.andM;Insert the disk containing the driver in drive A and push the Add button.andO;Select the desired printer driver(s) and choose the Add button; then open thePrint Manager window and leave the default PRINTER1 as the only setupprinter.andM;Select Setup Printers Change, remove the current driver and select the newdriver; select Change and OK, and then turn off the spooler by selectingSetup Spooler Disable Set.andM;Select Shutdown System and wait for a prompt to turn off the computer; turnthe power off, then on.andM;Open the Print Manager window and select Setup Spooler Enable Set.andP;  Again,select Shutdown System, wait for a prompt to turn off the system and then doso.andP;  The new printer driver is now ready to run.andP;  -- Bob Holmes</TEXT></DOC>